# Web API Conventions

## Response Format

Always use `ApiResponse<T>` wrapper:

```csharp
return Ok(new ApiResponse<DashboardSummary>
{
    Success = true,
    Data = summary
});
```

## JSON Serialization

- **PascalCase** property names (no camelCase conversion)
- Configured via `PropertyNamingPolicy = null`
- Frontend expects PascalCase: `response.Data.TotalLogsToday`

## Controllers

| Controller | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| `LogsController` | Search, export (CSV/Excel), CRUD |
| `DashboardController` | Summary stats, top computers, top errors |
| `SavedFiltersController` | CRUD for saved searches + preview |

## Search Pattern

```csharp
[HttpPost("search")]
public async Task<IActionResult> Search([FromBody] LogSearchRequest request)
{
    var criteria = MapToCriteria(request);
    var result = await _repository.SearchAsync(criteria);
    return Ok(new ApiResponse<PagedResult<LogEntry>> { Success = true, Data = result });
}
```

## Authentication

- DedgeAuth SSO (JWT tokens via `DedgeAuth.Client` library)
- `AddDedgeAuth()` / `UseDedgeAuth()` / `MapDedgeAuthProxy()` in `Program.cs`
- Role-based: `[RequireAppPermission("Admin")]` or standard `[Authorize]`
- Rate limiting: fixed window per user/host
- Full docs: `C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\docs\integration\`

## Static Files

`wwwroot/` served via:
```csharp
app.UseDefaultFiles();
app.UseStaticFiles();
```

**NEVER use `MapFallbackToFile("index.html")`** — this app uses separate HTML pages (not a SPA).
`MapFallbackToFile` prevents IIS from issuing its built-in trailing-slash redirect on virtual
application roots, which breaks all relative CSS/JS paths. See `Docs/CSS-Loading-Flow.md`.
